info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Freeze Warning issued September 27 at 9:33PM CDT until September 28 at 8:00AM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...FREEZE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM CDT WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...Sub-freezing temperatures as low as 28 expected. * WHERE...Portions of east central, north central and northeast Minnesota and north central and northwest Wisconsin. * WHEN...From midnight tonight to 8 AM CDT Wednesday. * IMPACTS...Frost and freeze conditions will kill crops, other sensitive vegetation and possibly damage unprotected outdoor plumbing. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Areas adjacent/near Lake Superior will likely remain above freezing but may still receive frost.
info.instruction: Take steps now to protect tender plants from the cold. To prevent freezing and possible bursting of outdoor water pipes they should be wrapped, drained, or allowed to drip slowly. Those that have in-ground sprinkler systems should drain them and cover above- ground pipes to protect them from freezing.
